''' Efthimis Kioumourtzoglou ''' (in '''{{lang-el|<U+0395><U+03C5><U+03B8><U+03CD><U+03BC><U+03B7><U+03C2> <U+039A><U+03B9><U+03BF><U+03C5><U+03BC><U+03BF><U+03C5><U+03C1><U+03C4><U+03B6><U+03CC><U+03B3><U+03BB><U+03BF><U+03C5>}}'''; born [[September 28]], [[1952]] in [[Greece]]) is a [[Greece|Greek]] professional [[basketball]] coach. He was the coach of the [[Greece national basketball team|Greek National Squad]] from 1987 to 1994. He won the silver medal at the [[Eurobasket 1989]]. 

He also won the 6th place at the [[1990 FIBA World Championship]], the 4th place at the [[Eurobasket 1993]] and the 4th place at the [[Eurobasket 1991]]. In 1995, he was a [[Euroleague]] semifinalist at the Saragoza final four and he managed to win the 3rd place there while coaching [[Panathinaikos BC]]. In 1996, he was a [[Saporta Cup|European Cup]] finalist while coaching [[PAOK BC]].

He was also the head coach of [[Panionios BC]], [[Aris BC]], and [[Iraklis BC]].

